<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,626,724]" pageId="4" pageNumber="213">
Widespread in Tasmania in wet forest, typically overgrowing bryophytes at the bases of old trees, especially species of the conifer 
<taxonomicName box="[265,381,662,688]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Athrotaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="213" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[265,381,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="213">Athrotaxis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; also known from 
<collectingCountry box="[594,745,662,689]" name="New Zealand" pageId="4" pageNumber="213">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and southern South America. 
<collectionCode box="[1085,1104,662,688]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="213" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
